  "explanation": "Periodic trends are specific patterns in the properties of elements within the periodic table, which are observable due to their position in a period or group. These trends explain why elements in a particular group react similarly and include properties such as atomic radius, ionization energy, electron affinity, and electronegativity. For example, atomic radius generally decreases from left to right across a period and increases down a group, while ionization energy tends to increase from left to right across a period and decrease down a group.",
